        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Greetings Dark Ones,</P><P>I just made level 4 last night and was checking out the new spells that are now available to me. I don't fully understand the various tactics available to us, but after looking at the level 4 spells, I had an idea and wanted to see if you thought it would work...</P><P>If I started with a Fear spell, then cast Clinging Darkness (I think that's the right name) to slow them down - and THEN sent my skeleton pet after them to beat on them while they were running... would that be a proper use of my abilities? Also - I didn't see it, but may have just missed it - is there a Fear versus Undead spell? Or does the regular Fear spell work on everything?</P><P>Please don't laugh - I'm still trying to figure all of this out. I hear references to "kiting", "fear-kiting" and "reverse-kiting" and don't understand it, so I'm really "in the dark"! (Pun intended) <img src=icon_smile_wink.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>I would greatly appreciate any advice you can give me. Thanks!</P><P><b><font color=purple><i>Lady Raivn</i></font id=purple></b><BR><font color=yellow>Necromaniac of the 4th Degree</font id=yellow></font></td>
