 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Suetekh</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The first undead fear is Spook the Dead at lvl 8 I think.  It uses a lot less mana than regular fear.  I really didnt start fear kiting mush until the high teens.  Mostly, I used the send in the pet, DoT, tank when pet low method.  <BR>Always keep dark pact up when fight, but watch your heath.  Tap when low.  You really don't get a good nuke for non-undead until 24, so you can use your life tap until then.  When you are full mana though, a pure nuke is more efficient.  Against undead you get Ward undead earlier (lvl 8 I think).  When DoTing, becarefull how many you hit the mob with.  Too many DoTs (3 or 4) will cause the MoB to agro you instead of pet.  <BR>A necromancer can usually solo yellows and maybe a low red.  You are usally better at this at the level you get a new pet and then the ability decreases as the pet ages until you get your next pet.  Yellow and reds will resist your spells more though.</P><P>Suetekh<BR>Necromancer of 24 Reanimations</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Azumaan Necromaan</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Here's my breakdown of a necros life over the course of spell ranks.</P><P><BR>Level 1: Just getting started. You have your trusty lifetap, pet, and your first DoT.</P><P>Level 4: Things really start to open up here. You have Clinging Darkness (snare + dmg), Poison Bolt (your first dmg-only DoT), an upgrade to your lifetap and pet, as well as the almighty Fear and Gate spells.</P><P>Level 8: The Utility level. Not many spells here that directly effect your fighting, just help make it easier. More importantly: your first hp to mana spell (Dark Pact), Gather Shadows (invis), Heal (Dark Empathy), Shadow Step, Pet Heal, etc. etc. lots of great stuff you'll be using for awhile.</P><P>Level 12: Finally, big upgrades to those weak level 4 spells, unfortunantly your stuck with these until level 29. You get your first pet-buff, corpse summon spell, undead-fear, and a Heal/Dmg over Time spell, and a much needed LifeTap upgrade.</P><P>Level 16: Another utility level. We get the all-powerful Feign Death at this level, as well as an undead-root, a debuff-DoT (Heart Flutter), an AE DoT (Infectious Cloud - meaning it can hit more than one target), we also get Cancel Magic (for getting rid of other peoples buffs if your dueling, or stuff you don't want on yourself) Shielding (to increase hp/ac/magic resist) Shieldskin (absorbs damage) and Spirit Armor (ac buff, best in game for the level [Clerics don't get this spell until level 19 :)])</P><P>Level 20: Another semi-utility level. an upgrade to Dark Pact (Allure of Death), an undead-charm, nuke, and slow, Harmshield (makes you invulnerable to everything for 18 seconds, you can't cast or do anything but run), also, a huge upgrade to LifeTap (doing over 60 damage at level 20, reaching 75 eventually)</P><P>Level 24: Great new pet (which we get every spell level btw), a new pet-buff, more hp buffs for ourselves, the invaluable Screaming Terror (mez + memblur [sometimes]), Shock of Poison (our first real DD), and the bane of all necros: Rapacious Subversion (commonly known as "twitch")</P><P>Level 29: God level. Humongous upgrades to our DoTs, a duel wielding pet, a big new undead-nuke and DoT, a big big lifetap (will do 150dmg eventually), a new pet-heal, and heal-self over time spell (upgrade to lvl 12 Leach), and a new Point Blank Area of Effect spell (PBAoE - hits EVERYTHING in a small radius around you)</P><P>Level 34: Root! 'Nuff said about this level, necro's life changes (though with the new pet changes this isn't quite as dramatic), we also get a fast-acting new DoT (Venom of the Snake), an upgrade to Fear, a new skeleton-illusion hp to mana (lich) spell, more self-hp buffs, and an upgrade to Shock of Poison (Torbas Acid Blast)</P><P><BR>This is all I know..since I'm only level 33, but I hope this helps!!</P><P><font size=1><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="_blank">Azumaan</a></b><br>33 Erudite Necromancer<br>Silver Faith<br>Mithaniel Marr</font id=size1></font></td>
      </tr>
